"n.染色体 【记】 chrom(颜色)+o+some( 体); 参考: somatic(身体的) n. 染色体(DNA链, 携带了传递遗传信息的基因和功能团) 【记】chrom颜色, some体－染色体. 参: somatic(adj 肉体的) 【记】chrom 颜色,色素 + some 体 chromosome (n.)  1889, from German Chromosom, coined 1888 by German anatomist Wilhelm von Waldeyer-Hartz (1836-1921), from Latinized form of Greek khroma ""color"" (see chroma) + -some (3)). So called because the structures contain a substance that stains readily with basic dyes."
